===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|abbesse|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|abaesse|lang=fro}}, {{term|abeesse|lang=fro}} (French {{term|abbesse|lang=fr}}), from {{etyl|la}} {{term|abbatissa|lang=la}}, feminine of {{term|abbas|lang=la}}, {{term|abbatis||abbot|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/ˈæb.ɪs/|/ˈæb.əs/}}
* {{audio|en-us-abbess.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# A female superior or [[governess]] of a [[nunnery]], or [[convent]] of nuns, having the same authority over the nuns which the [[abbots]] have over the monks.
#: ''The ''abbess'' was always after the nuns to keep the convent immaculately clean.''

